data-triple-N3.o: "Bengal is a historical and geographical region in the east region of the Indian subcontinent at the apex of the Bay of Bengal. Today, it is mainly divided between the country of Bangladesh and the state of West Bengal in India, although some regions of the previous kingdoms of Bengal (during local monarchical regimes and British rule) are now part of the neighbouring Indian states of Bihar, Jharkhand, Assam, Tripura and Odisha."@en
